{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Fluid Sim 3D",
  "description": "Volumetric 3D particle compute fluid simulation — decomposed from `FluidSimulation3DGenerator` + the four fluid_*_3d shaders into the curated primitive library. Built on the new Camera-port shape (PortType::Camera, node.camera_orbit) so the camera basis lives in one node feeding both the volume sim (cam.fwd drives flatten) and the display projector (camera_orbit → scatter_particles_camera).\n\nPer-frame pipeline:\n1. Volume buildup: seed→scatter_3d→resolve_3d→blur_3d ×3 (density volume) → fluid_gradient_curl_3d → blur_3d ×3 (vector field).\n2. Simulate: fluid_simulate_3d consumes (aliased in particles, blurred field, blurred density) and mutates positions in place. Uses cam.fwd for the flatten-toward-camera math.\n3. Display: seed.particles (aliased — already mutated by simulate) → scatter_particles_camera (mode dispatched by container — None→Orthographic toroidal wrap, else Perspective) → resolve_accumulator → reinhard_tone_map → affine_transform → final_output.\n\nClip-trigger envelope: same structural shape as FluidSim2D — trigger_gate gates raw trigger_count by `clip_trigger > 0.5`; envelope_decay (rate 12.0) produces a one-shot 0→1 envelope per gated edge; sample_and_hold latches the mode slider at trigger time. Five modes:\n- mode 0 (turbulence burst): turbulence *= 1 + 9*env\n- mode 1 (curl rotation): curl_angle += π * env\n- mode 2 (flow sign-flip): flow *= 1 - 2*env\n- mode 3 (re-seed): trigger_gate(clip_trigger AND mode==3) → fluid_seed_3d.trigger + simulate.trigger; clip_trigger_cycle(mod=8) drives pattern (8 patterns: 7 geometric + Random)\n- mode 4 (3D inject): inject_burst.active gates clip_trigger_cycle(mod=4) → mux to either the cycled zone index (active=1) or -1 (active=0) → simulate.inject_index; the four zones are hardcoded tetrahedron vertices in the shader\n\nKnown parity deltas vs legacy:\n(1) Volume pipeline runs every frame; legacy amortized to every-other-frame to halve GPU cost on the volume passes. Graph runtime lacks per-frame sub-graph gating (same shape as FluidSim2D's mode-3 hitch). ~30–40% extra GPU on the volume passes.\n(2) vol_res baked at 128 — the legacy 64/128/256 slider is dropped because the graph runtime can't reallocate Texture3D mid-frame.\n(3) Display tone curve UV recenter is a separate affine_transform pass instead of fused into the tone shader — mathematically equivalent, not byte-exact (same delta as FluidSim2D).\n(4) The mode-3 re-seed will produce a ~16ms GPU pipeline hitch on each fire; legacy skipped the full pipeline on seed frames via the trigger port. The trigger-port skip is supported here (fluid_simulate_3d.trigger), but the volume pipeline still runs that frame — acceptable.\n\nCamera wiring: rotate_x (legacy [-1, +1] slider) → ×π → camera_orbit.tilt; rotate_y → ×π → camera_orbit.orbit; rotate_z → ×π → camera_orbit.roll (new in Camera struct); cam_dist → camera_orbit.distance. fov is baked at π/3 ≈ 60° to match the legacy implicit FOV.",
